    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{1}{x-1}-\frac{2}{x^{2}-1}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{1}{x+1}, x\ne 1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{1}{x-1}-\frac{2}{x^{2}-1}} 
      \amp = {\frac{1}{x-1}}-\frac{2}{(x - 1)(x + 1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{1\cdot({x+1})}{({x-1})\cdot({x+1})} -\frac{2}{(x - 1)(x + 1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{x+1-2}}{(x - 1)(x + 1)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{x-1}}{(x - 1)(x + 1)} \\
      \amp = {\frac{1}{x+1}, x\ne 1}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{x-1}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>x \ne {1}</m>.</p>
</solution>
